The article is a transcript of a press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney, Secretary of Interior Ken Salazar, and Deputy Assistant to the President Heather Zichal. They discuss the Blueprint for a Secure Energy Future, which is a one-year progress report that was provided to the President. The report highlights achievements in reducing oil imports, increasing fuel efficiency standards, and promoting renewable energy generation. Secretary Salazar also discusses the increase in domestic oil and gas production and the plans for future lease sales. The briefing also touches on other topics such as the shootings in Afghanistan and the President's meeting with Mayor Bloomberg.